By Ngozi Njoku Lagos – An Ogudu Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State on Thursday remanded a painter, Tobi Kechiku, who pleaded guilty to  membership of a secret cult called Eiye confraternity. The Magistrate, Mrs Bukola Mogaji, remanded 24-year-old Kechiku in prison and adjourned the case until Sept. 6 for review of the facts and sentencing. Earlier, the Prosecutor, Insp. Donjour Perezi, told the court that the defendant committed the offences on Aug. 2 on Governor Road, Ikotun, Lagos. Perezi said that the police received formation that the defendant and some others  were fighting at Ikotun; when they got there, the defendant and some others were arrested. “They were arrested without weapons but the defendant made  a confessional statement to the police that he joined the confraternity in 2018 at a village called Agodi in Abeokuta. According to the prosecutor, the offence contravened Sections 42(a) of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015.